---
description: Apply consistent UI-stack design-system standards for spacing, typography, color, interaction states, and accessibility.
alwaysApply: true
---

- Use a consistent spacing scale (8px-based rhythm) across layout and components.
- Maintain clear color hierarchy with semantic states and dark-mode-safe mappings.
- Use consistent type scale and readable line-height for body and headings.
- Ensure interactive elements include default, hover, active, focus, and disabled states.
- Enforce accessibility basics: semantic elements, contrast, keyboard access, and adequate touch targets.
- Respect reduced-motion preferences for animations and transitions.
